  "texts": [
    "Notice that if the chosen node j is new, then also the traversed edge (i, j) is necessarily new as well.",
    "Therefore, in this case there is also a triggering of ν 2 + 1 edges from j to other previously visited nodes, as before.",
    "Finally, in this manuscript, we let the initial graph G 0 be a small graph that emulates the triggering mechanism introduced, shown in Fig.",
    "This is a regular tree with branching parameter ν 1 + 1 and two levels, where only the leaves are considered new, since all other nodes have already triggered.",
    "In other words, a root node has triggered ν 1 + 1 nodes connected to it, and again these nodes have also triggered each ν 1 + 1 other nodes."
